{
    "name": "Librarian",
    "type": "npc",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Librarian",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 240
                }
            ],
            "html": "Keepers of knowledge, librarians document discoveries, events, and laws. The best librarians record events twice; once for public record, and again to record how events truly unfolded. A librarian typically knows four to six additional languages, often including <a aonid=\"4\" game-obj=\"Languages\">Elven</a> and <a aonid=\"2\" game-obj=\"Languages\">Draconic</a>. A librarian is a 3rd-level challenge for encounters involving research.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Humanoid</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"14\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Society</a></u>)</b>: DC 13"
        },
        {
            "name": "Scholars",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Centers Of Learning",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 240
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "locations",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Locations",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Locations",
                        "image": "Sidebar_3_Locations.png"
                    },
                    "html": ""
                },
                {
                    "name": "Kitharodian Academy (Taldor)",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 240
                        }
                    ],
                    "html": ": Famed bardic college teaching students of all social classes. <br/><b>Magaambya (Nantambu)</b>: Ancient school with some of the world's greatest stores of arcane knowledge. <br/><b>University of Lepidstadt (Ustalav)</b>: School primarily focusing on alchemy, medicine, and scientific study."
                },
                {
                    "name": "Uncommon Scholastic Disciplines",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 240
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    },
                    "html": "Beside the life and natural sciences such as arcana, biology, botany, geology, oceanography, and zoology, demand is increasing in cities for more modern disciplines, like anthropology, economics, sociology, urban planning, and even art curation and forensic investigation."
                }
            ],
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 240",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 240
                }
            ],
            "html": "True power comes from knowledge: the power to shape the growth of kingdoms by mere whispers, staying three steps ahead of adversaries, or even knowing which flora is best for creating untraceable poisons."
        }
    ],
